  "name": "Volume Spike EMA Strategy",
  "description": "This algorithm identifies significant volume spikes by comparing current trading volume to a 30-period moving average of volume on a 15-minute timeframe. A long entry is triggered when the current volume exceeds 2.5 times the moving average and the closing price is above the 20-period EMA, aiming to capitalize on momentum shifts.",
  "algorithm_type": "EventDriven",
  "prompt": "Develop an intermediate-level EventDriven trading algorithm in Python that detects significant volume spikes compared to a 30-period moving average of volume on the 15-minute timeframe. The strategy should generate a long entry when current volume exceeds 2.5 times the 30-period moving average of volume, and the closing price is above the 20-period Exponential Moving Average (EMA). Exit the position when the closing price crosses below the 20-period EMA or a loss of 1.5% is reached. Ensure that the algorithm ignores signals during the first 30 minutes of the trading session each day.",
